Text: You really should have an `ArrayList` of objects in some kind of level or handler `class` to deal with having multiple objects. That way you can easily `add` or `remove` them as you need to using the `ArrayList` functions `add()` and `remove()`. For more specific information on actually removing objects see this [post](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/30420793/removing-object-from-game-in-java-eclipse/30430905#30430905). And for information on handling objects in a game see this [post](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/30443458/spawning-mutiple-circles-and-make-them-move/30443968#30443968).

You really should have an `ArrayList` of objects in some kind of level or handler `class` to deal with having multiple objects. That way you can easily `add` or `remove` them as you need to using the `ArrayList` functions `add()` and `remove()`. For more specific information on actually removing objects see this [post](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/30420793/removing-object-from-game-in-java-eclipse/30430905#30430905). And for information on handling objects in a game see this [post](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/30443458/spawning-mutiple-circles-and-make-them-move/30443968#30443968).
